The paper discusses mixed-signal hardware accelerators for deep learning, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The focus on neural networks and their sensitivity to hardware-specific noise suggests that it could also belong to Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) or Architecture (cs.AR). The evaluation of the model's accuracy on the CIFAR-10 dataset suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
